        "$:/plugins/twpub/112af7d90f46baad/text/000000945": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/112af7d90f46baad/text/000000945",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-112af7d90f46baad-58df80 twpub-112af7d90f46baad-25d4bc twpub-112af7d90f46baad-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/112af7d90f46baad/text/000000616\"><span class=\"label\">[31]</span></$link> P. 122. This same curiously inept criticism of the war which cost France her American provinces occurs in Voltaire's <i>Memoirs</i>, wherein he says, &quot;In 1756 England made a piratical war upon France for some acres of snow.&quot; See also his <i>PrÃ©cis du SiÃ¨cle de Louis</i> XV.</p></div></div>"
